-- Оі(k) = Оұ(n) and ОІ(m) where (n,m) = unpair(k).
-- If P вҶ’ Q then for each (n,m): either Оұ(n)=false (so and=false),
-- or Оұ(n)=true so P holds, Q holds, ОІ(m)=false (so and=false).
-- Conversely, if вҲҖk.Оі(k)=false and P holds (witness nвӮҖ with Оұ(nвӮҖ)=true),
-- then Оұ(nвӮҖ) and ОІ(m) = false for all m, so ОІ(m)=false, so Q.

openвҶ’closed-is-closed : (P Q : hProp в„“-zero) вҶ’
